28    /**
29    * Defines the flags that are provided to any {@code ClassWriter} when writing a class. Typically, this gives opportunity to instruct ASM
30    * to compute stack map frames or the size of the local variables array and the operand stack. If no specific flags are required for
31    * applying this wrapper, the given value is to be returned.
32    *
33    * @param flags The currently set flags. This value should be combined (e.g. {@code flags | foo}) into the value that is returned by this wrapper.
34    * @return The flags to be provided to the ASM {@code ClassWriter}.
35    */
36    int mergeWriter(int flags);
37   
38    /**
39    * Defines the flags that are provided to any {@code ClassReader} when reading a class if applicable. Typically, this gives opportunity to
40    * instruct ASM to expand or skip frames and to skip code and debug information. If no specific flags are required for applying this
41    * wrapper, the given value is to be returned.
42    *
43    * @param flags The currently set flags. This value should be combined (e.g. {@code flags | foo}) into the value that is returned by this wrapper.
44    * @return The flags to be provided to the ASM {@code ClassReader}.
45    */
46    int mergeReader(int flags);
